title.narrative: Equitable access to quality education opportunities provided

description.narrative: To strengthen access to education and improve quality, UNICEF provided learning services to 147,927 children in non-formal and educational supplies to 1,273,002 children in formal settings. 61% of the people-in-need reached were from high (Levels 4-6) severity areas. For children who have been out-of-school, UNICEF increased access through supporting 55,131 children in self-learning programme (SLP) and conducted ‘Back to Learning' activities reaching 198,813 adults and children to raise awareness of available educational pathways. To increase the quality of education, UNICEF supported the training of 39,615 teachers. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/01/2020
